techmeme.title: Lenovo reports Q4 revenue up 9% YoY to $13.8B, vs. $13B est., second straight quarter of revenue growth, and net profit up 118% YoY to $248M, vs. $162M est. (Josh Ye/Reuters)
US-listed PDD, which runs Temu and Pinduoduo, reports Q1 revenue up 131% YoY to ~$12B and operating profit up 275% YoY to ~$3.6B, as global expansion gains pace (Sarah Zheng/Bloomberg)
South Korea announces a ~$19B support package for the domestic chip industry and asks the industry ministry to strengthen the country's non-memory chip sector (Reuters)
Source: the US DOJ and state AGs plan to sue Live Nation on Thursday for illegally abusing its live ticketing monopoly through its 2010 Ticketmaster acquisition (Sara Fischer/Axios)
LA-based Aerodome, which uses autonomous drones to help first responders get a view of problems like crimes and fires, raised a $21.5M Series A led by CRV (Brian Heater/TechCrunch)
